The invention relates to the field of 3D display technology, in particular to a 3D browser comprising an observation room, a supporting panel, and an observation panel. The supporting panel is disposed at the rear end in the observation room, and is used for supporting a display device and averagely dividing a display zone of the display device into a left-eye zone and a right-eye zone. The observation panel is disposed at the front end in the observation room and a left-eye lens and a right-eye lens are disposed on the observation panel at intervals. The light of a length-compressed left image from the left-eye zone enters the left-eye lens, while the light of a length-compressed right image from the right-eye zone enters the right-eye lens. Length magnifying power of the left-eye lens to the left-eye image and length magnifying power of the right-eye lens to the right-eye image are more than width magnifying power of the left-eye lens to the left-eye image and width magnifying power of the right-eye lens to the right-eye image. The left-eye image is amplified by the left-eye lens while the right-eye image is amplified by the right-eye lens, and then both the left-eye image and the right-eye image enter eyes to present an amplified 3D image similar to reality. By the above manner, the 3D browser with a simple structure is capable of really recovering an original 3D image and is easy for a user to use.
